-among-ace-eddie-award-nominees-full-list-1201390870/|title='American Sniper', 'Boyhood', 'Gone Girl' Among ACE Eddie Award Nominees (FULL LIST)|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=January 2, 2015|accessdate=January 2, 2015|first=Dave|last=McNary}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[American Film Institute Awards 2014]]\n| Top Ten Films of the Year\n| \n| {{won}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"AFI\">{{cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/afi-list-top-ten-films-754933|title=AFI List of Top Ten Films Expands to Include 11 Movies|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=December 9, 2014|accessdate=December 9, 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=row rowspan=\"2\"| [[British Academy Film Awards]]\n| [[BAFTA Award for Best Adapted Screenplay|Best Adapted Screenplay]]\n| Jason Hall\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2015/01/bafta-nominations-2015-baftas-nominees-full-list-1201344262/|title=BAFTA Nominations: 'Grand Budapest Hotel' Leads With 11 \u2013 Full List|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=January 8, 2015|accessdate=January 9, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[BAFTA Award for Best Sound|Best Sound]]\n| Walt Martin, John Reitz, Gregg Rudloff, Alan Robert Murray, Bub Asman\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Cinema Audio Society Awards]]\n| Outstanding Achievement in Sound Mixing for a Motion Picture \u2013 Live Action\n| Walt Martin, Gregg Rudloff, John Reitz, Robert Fernandez, Thomas J. O'Connell, James Ashwell\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.indiewire.com/thompsononhollywood/cinema-audio-society-nominates-american-sniper-true-detective-and-more-20150113|title=Cinema Audio Society Nominates 'American Sniper', 'True Detective' and More|website=[[Indiewire]]|date=January 13, 2015|accessdate=January 13, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150130141225/http://blogs.indiewire.com/thompsononhollywood/cinema-audio-society-nominates-american-sniper-true-de